1
00:00:08,360 --> 00:00:10,491
Go, go! Break away!

2
00:00:10,605 --> 00:00:12,570
This is the last one, Pops!

3
00:00:12,628 --> 00:00:16,308
Ran will get mad at me if you run out of money!

4
00:00:16,948 --> 00:00:19,520
Keep a close eye on him, Conan.

5
00:00:19,931 --> 00:00:22,697
He just got paid,

6
00:00:23,028 --> 00:00:26,068
and he gambled away all of it in just half a day the other day.

7
00:00:26,388 --> 00:00:29,680
Not only that, but that's actually my money.

8
00:00:30,491 --> 00:00:31,988
Got it, Conan?

9
00:00:32,468 --> 00:00:33,840
Got it.

10
00:00:34,514 --> 00:00:35,622
Pops!

11
00:00:35,790 --> 00:00:38,388
Shut up. I know.

12
00:00:38,525 --> 00:00:39,268
Yes, yes!

13
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:43,508
Yes! Yes, yes, yes!

14
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:44,400
All right!

15
00:00:48,971 --> 00:00:51,074
What? You must be joking.

16
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:58,994
Here's the problem, should I man up and...

17
00:00:59,325 --> 00:01:01,497
Yeah, and go home.

18
00:01:01,737 --> 00:01:03,760
Should I bet the rest of my money?

19
00:01:03,862 --> 00:01:05,908
Or drink my sorrows away?

20
00:01:05,965 --> 00:01:07,451
Now that's the problem.

21
00:01:08,297 --> 00:01:10,697
Both would be huge problems.

22
00:01:12,468 --> 00:01:13,565
Excuse me.

23
00:01:14,251 --> 00:01:17,291
Are you the great detective, Kogoro Mouri?

24
00:01:17,508 --> 00:01:18,297
-What? -What?

25
00:01:18,925 --> 00:01:22,251
Indeed. I am the great detective, Mouri.

26
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:26,777
Excuse me. I'm unfortunately out of business cards.

27
00:01:27,405 --> 00:01:30,400
I'm a freelance horse racing journalist.

28
00:01:30,868 --> 00:01:34,022
I'd like to hire you for a job.

29
00:01:34,285 --> 00:01:36,891
Yes, yes. More gambling money.

30
00:01:40,925 --> 00:01:42,411
In my eyes are maximum creation.

31
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,274
My detective skills are tomorrow's reaction.

32
00:01:44,330 --> 00:01:45,748
He keeps talking about gambling money,

33
00:01:45,805 --> 00:01:47,977
but there's something fishy about all these horse racing jobs.

34
00:01:47,977 --> 00:01:49,565
He sees through the one and only truth.

35
00:01:49,611 --> 00:01:51,268
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

36
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:53,440
His name is Detective Conan!

37
00:03:41,050 --> 00:03:46,840
"The Thoroughbred Kidnapping Case (Part 1)"

38
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:49,430
"Mouri Detective Agency" -We're home.

39
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:50,560
We're back.

40
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,930
Dad, hurry.

41
00:03:52,930 --> 00:03:54,350
What?

42
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:56,640
You have a client, dad.

43
00:03:57,650 --> 00:03:59,860
Well, well.

44
00:04:03,940 --> 00:04:05,650
Thank for you waiting.

45
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:09,030
I am the great detective, Kogoro Mouri.

46
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:12,950
Excuse me. I'm unfortunately out of business cards.

47
00:04:12,950 --> 00:04:17,830
I write horse racing predictions and reviews online.

48
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:20,960
I'd like to ask you to do something for me.

49
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:23,460
Business is booming!

50
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:28,130
Are you sure, Pops?

51
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:30,930
That job was the same as the last one.

52
00:04:33,350 --> 00:04:38,230
Excuse me, but I'm a huge horse racing fan.

53
00:04:38,230 --> 00:04:40,560
I'd actually like to hire you.

54
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,070
What? What?

55
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:54,950
Anyway, that's that.

56
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:57,160
Thank you, detective.

57
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,930
What's going on?

58
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,640
We did it.

59
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,850
Yeah. Now we can relax.

60
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:21,060
You're right.

61
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:24,430
With a famous detective on the case, surely...

62
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,040
I don't know what's going on,

63
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,660
