144
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:59,640
"Construction 50m Ahead Detour" -What's wrong? Hey, you can't just...

145
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,060
What?

146
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,440
Follow that car.

147
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,450
Where'd the trailer go?

148
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:20,040
What's wrong?

149
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:22,120
There's construction up ahead.

150
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:25,340
That sign was placed incorrectly.

151
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:33,050
I'm sorry. Thank you for waiting.

152
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:36,140
What a waste of time.

153
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:38,560
Now, now. We have time.

154
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,430
Let's take it slowly.

155
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:44,940
What is it?

156
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:47,440
Something not right.

157
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,030
I have a bad feeling about this.

158
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:53,660
"Okuho Horse Track"

159
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:06,130
I'm glad he's all right.

160
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:11,760
Nothing's gonna happen with the great detective, Kogoro Mouri on the job.

161
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:13,130
It's not him.

162
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:16,640
-What? -This isn't White Spirits.

163
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:17,720
What?

164
00:12:19,060 --> 00:12:22,730
"White Spirits"

165
00:12:31,337 --> 00:12:32,463
I knew it.

166
00:12:32,463 --> 00:12:33,422
You're right.

167
00:12:33,422 --> 00:12:35,007
There's no construction happening at all.

168
00:12:35,007 --> 00:12:37,218
This is ridiculous.

169
00:12:37,218 --> 00:12:38,260
Look.

170
00:12:40,596 --> 00:12:42,306
Is that...

171
00:12:42,306 --> 00:12:43,557
Yeah.

172
00:12:43,557 --> 00:12:50,397
They're tire marks from the real trailer the culprit drove away

173
00:12:50,397 --> 00:12:55,361
after the driver Shiomi got into the other trailer.

174
00:12:56,737 --> 00:12:58,447
What's wrong, Conan?

175
00:12:58,447 --> 00:12:59,824
Nothing.

176
00:12:59,824 --> 00:13:03,035
I was just thinking this is like that other case.

177
00:13:03,035 --> 00:13:05,788
What? This has happened before?

178
00:13:05,788 --> 00:13:10,835
It's called the "The Adventure of Silver Blaze".

179
00:13:10,835 --> 00:13:14,964
What's that? I've never heard of it.

180
00:13:14,964 --> 00:13:19,760
It's a Sherlock Holmes story written by Conan Doyle.

181
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:22,596
You're talking about a book?

182
00:13:22,596 --> 00:13:24,431
What nonsense.

183
00:13:25,641 --> 00:13:27,643
I hope that's all it is.

184
00:13:30,896 --> 00:13:32,731
Hello?

185
00:13:32,731 --> 00:13:35,442
Oh, Takagi.

186
00:13:35,442 --> 00:13:37,153
That's good.

187
00:13:37,153 --> 00:13:38,988
Any leads on the suspect?

188
00:13:40,447 --> 00:13:43,617
I see. We'll meet you right away.

189
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:46,537
Was that Officer Takagi?

190
00:13:46,537 --> 00:13:51,250
Yeah. The driver Shiomi's wife and child were released,

191
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:54,336
and made it back home.

192
00:13:54,336 --> 00:13:56,297
But they were blindfolded,

193
00:13:56,297 --> 00:13:59,216
so they don't know anything about the culprit.

194
00:13:59,216 --> 00:14:00,634
I see.

195
00:14:00,634 --> 00:14:02,553
I'm glad they're all right, though.

196
00:14:04,555 --> 00:14:06,432
"Kozo Tokuyoshi"

197
00:14:10,144 --> 00:14:13,147
Leave! Leave me!

198
00:14:13,147 --> 00:14:15,733
Can't you read this?

199
00:14:16,901 --> 00:14:19,111
Let me see that.

200
00:14:19,111 --> 00:14:19,278
"In one hour, come alone to the fountain at Tsubaki Park."

201
00:14:19,278 --> 00:14:19,320
I knew it.
"In one hour, come alone to the fountain at Tsubaki Park."

202
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,446
"In one hour, come alone to the fountain at Tsubaki Park."

203
00:14:20,446 --> 00:14:21,989
"Bring the 100 million yen with you."

204
00:14:21,989 --> 00:14:24,992
"If anyone else comes, other than the president,"

205
00:14:24,992 --> 00:14:26,619
"White Spirits will not return forever."

206
00:14:27,912 --> 00:14:29,413
What is this?

207
00:14:29,413 --> 00:14:35,002
Tokuyoshi found it in his mailbox.

208
00:14:35,002 --> 00:14:37,922
He said he was going out alone

209
00:14:37,922 --> 00:14:42,301
with White Spirits' 100 million yen ransom.

210
00:14:42,301 --> 00:14:44,637
Without our protection.

211
00:14:44,637 --> 00:14:48,390
He what? That's too dangerous.

212
00:14:48,390 --> 00:14:52,019
We said the same thing.

213
00:14:52,019 --> 00:14:55,397
Danger? Protection?

214
00:14:55,397 --> 00:14:58,692
It's all just to arrest the culprit.

215
00:14:58,692 --> 00:15:01,737
I can't trust the police or detectives.

216
00:15:01,737 --> 00:15:05,658
If you follow me, I'll sue all of you.

217
00:15:05,658 --> 00:15:07,409
Don't forget that!

218
00:15:17,836 --> 00:15:19,088
Inspector.

219
00:15:19,088 --> 00:15:20,589
Of course.

220
00:15:20,589 --> 00:15:25,010
We can't ignore a crime happening right before our eyes.

221
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:26,720
We'll follow them carefully

222
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:29,598
so neither the culprit nor Tokuyoshi notice.

223
00:15:29,598 --> 00:15:30,683
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

224
00:16:06,302 --> 00:16:08,304
What is this?

225
00:16:08,304 --> 00:16:13,517
WS, KM North ST.

226
00:16:13,517 --> 00:16:15,102
WS...

227
00:16:15,102 --> 00:16:17,646
WS?

228
00:16:17,646 --> 00:16:21,900
Maybe they're referring to White Spirits.

229
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:23,319
That must be it.

230
00:16:23,319 --> 00:16:28,907
In other words, White Spirits is at KM North ST.

231
00:16:28,907 --> 00:16:30,993
Where is that?

232
00:16:30,993 --> 00:16:36,081
I wonder what word is normally abbreviated as ST.

233
00:16:36,081 --> 00:16:38,417
Station. The train station.

234
00:16:38,417 --> 00:16:39,418
I see.

235
00:16:39,418 --> 00:16:40,919
KM North...

236
00:16:40,919 --> 00:16:42,588
Katsumata North Station.

237
00:16:42,588 --> 00:16:44,048
Let's go.

238
00:16:44,048 --> 00:16:47,092
"Katsumata North Station"

239
00:16:52,014 --> 00:16:57,936
Kozo Tokuyoshi from Yagiri-cho, you have a message.

240
